# GPT-2 Text Generation 

##  Overview
This project demonstrates text generation using the GPT-2 (Generative Pre-trained Transformer 2) model.  
It generates human-like text based on a given input prompt using a pretrained deep learning model.

---

##  Objective
- To understand how transformer-based models work
- To generate meaningful text using a pretrained GPT-2 model
- To explore Natural Language Processing (NLP)

---

## Technologies Used
- Python
- Transformers (Hugging Face)
- PyTorch
- NumPy

---

##  Working Process
1. Load pretrained GPT-2 model
2. Provide an input prompt
3. Generate text using the model
4. Display the generated output

---

## Sample Code
```python
from transformers import GPT2LMHeadModel, GPT2Tokenizer

tokenizer = GPT2Tokenizer.from_pretrained('gpt2')
model = GPT2LMHeadModel.from_pretrained('gpt2')

input_text = "Artificial Intelligence is"
inputs = tokenizer.encode(input_text, return_tensors='pt')

outputs = model.generate(inputs, max_length=50, num_return_sequences=1)

print(tokenizer.decode(outputs[0]))
